entity.description:
Melvin Carter won his re-election as the mayor of St. Paul with 61% of first-choice votes. In Minneapolis, the mayoral voting count continued on Wednesday, November 3, after incumbent Mayor Jacob Frey fell short of the required 50% of the first-choice votes threshold in the first round of counting. However, Minneapolis voters decidedly voted against a proposed plan to overhaul policing in the city, according to MPR News.

Keep it here for news and updates.
